The paper deals with algorithmic problems related to graph theory, specifically the $k$-domination and total $k$-domination problems in interval graphs. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). However, since the focus is on developing faster algorithms for these problems, cs.DS and cs.DM are the most likely sub-categories. The use of interval graphs also suggests cs.CG as a possible sub-category. Finally, the mention of NP-hardness and solvability in certain graph classes suggests cs.CC and cs.GT as less likely but still possible sub-categories.
